Question:
Convert all strings in a list to uppercase.

Input:
List<String> list = Arrays.asList("apple", "banana", "cherry");

Solution:-
Java 8 Streams convert strings to uppercase using map(String::toUpperCase). For input ["apple", "banana", "cherry"], it prints APPLE, BANANA, CHERRY on separate lines.

#Step-by-Step Logic
Stream the list with stream(). Apply map(String::toUpperCase) to transform each string. Terminate with forEach(System.out::println) to print uppercase versions.
​
#Complete Implementation

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;

public class UppercaseStrings {
    public static void printUppercase(List<String> strings) {
        strings.stream()
               .map(String::toUpperCase)
               .forEach(System.out::println);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<String> list = Arrays.asList("apple", "banana", "cherry");
        printUppercase(list);
    }
}

Prints each uppercase string on new line. Method reference simplifies lambda.
​

#Thought Process
map transforms 1:1; String::toUpperCase standard for case change. forEach terminal for side-effect printing. Original list unchanged; stream creates new values lazily.
​

#Edge Cases Analysis
Empty list: No output.​
Null list: NPE on stream(); null-check.
Null elements: toUpperCase() on null → NPE; filter Objects::nonNull.
Empty strings: "" → "".
Mixed case: "Apple" → "APPLE".
Non-ASCII: Locale-sensitive, defaults JVM locale; specify toUpperCase(Locale) if needed. Large lists: Sequential fine; parallel for throughput.
